parameters:
If we had a Fishing Rod, it looks like we could catch some
fish here...

Alright, let's fish! (Remaining bait \V[57])Press enter in
sync with the sound cue
...No good. Looks like I was a bit too late.
It got away. Was I too early...?

Huh, I'm out of bait. I'm pretty sure the tool shop was
selling some. I need to go buy more...
--\c[17]Fruit of Attack Power\c[0] has been obtained!

The Great Buddha that sits here is a famous attraction. When
spring comes, it becomes a bustling spot for cherry blossom
viewing.

Sorry, but I'm planning to close up shop for a while. It's
not exactly a situation where I can be giving acupressure
treatments...

Eek!? A cat--!? [Author's note: Initially, it was set that
Nezumi Komachi would be scared of cats--]

Meow~n \I[15] (Ufufu, cats are so cute) [Since there were
already many cats placed on the map, it was troublesome so
the setting was abandoned...]

I love gazing at the pond from this hill. I walked here from
Fukagawa, bringing a lunchbox for a stroll.

I've let the laundry pile up too much... I'm in the middle
of washing it on my day off.

I couldn't believe it at first when I heard that demons were
attacking, but after seeing so many soldiers getting treated
at the clinic, I realized it wasn't a lie.
This is Ueno. If you go east, you'll reach Asakusa.

The woman named Kachou-san, who recently moved here, loves
flowers. The tenement has become very lively because of
that.
We were lucky that no demons came this way.
Huh...? Was there a sweet shop near Shinobazu Pond?

There used to be a fox teahouse right here until recently...
Now it's turned back into a meadow, almost as if we've been
bewitched by a fox.
Wow...! There are so many rare animals!

I heard that the castle has caught fire. What's going to
happen now... I'm very anxious.

It's my dream to build a zoo here. If you find any unusual
animals, please bring them to me. I'll welcome them.

Thanks to you, the number of animals has increased. If you
find more, please bring them here

The number of animals has increased, and now it has become a
splendid zoo. Thank you very much. This is a token of our
gratitude. Please accept it.

--As a token of thanks, you've received the \c[17]Beast God
Hairpin\c[0]!
--Oh! Is that a \c[17]pig\c[0]? Could I buy it for 1500 mon?
Not a problem. Please take good care of it
Thank you! I'll display it in the zoo right away!

Hmm, that's a shame... If you change your mind, please let
me know.

--Oh! Is that a \c[17]Tanuki\c[0]? Could I buy it for 2000
mon?
Not a problem. Please take good care of it
Thank you! I'll display it in the zoo right away!

Hmm, that's too bad... If you change your mind, please let
me have it.

--Oh! Is that a \c[17]goat\c[0]? Could I buy it for 2500

Not a problem. Please take good care of it
Thank you! I'll display it in the zoo right away!

Hmm, that's too bad... If you change your mind, please let

Not a problem. Please take good care of it.
Thank you! I'll display it in the zoo right away!

Hmm, that's a shame... If you change your mind, please let

--Oh! Is that a \c[17]camel\c[0]? Could I buy it for 3500
mon?
That's fine. Please take good care of it
Thank you! I'll display it in the zoo right away!

Hmm, that's a shame... If you change your mind, please let

--Oh! Is that a \c[17]Snow Monkey\c[0]? Could I buy it for
4000 mon?
Not a problem. Please take good care of it
Thank you! I'll display it in the zoo right away!

Hmm, that's a shame... If you change your mind, please let

--Oh! Is that a \c[17]Water Buffalo\c[0]? Could I buy it for
5000 mon?
Not a problem. Please take good care of it
Thank you! I'll display it in the zoo right away!

Hmm, that's too bad... If you change your mind, please let
me know.

--Oh! Is that a \c[17]tiger\c[0]? What a magnificent
creature...! Would you sell it for 8000 mon?
Not a problem. Please take good care of it
Thank you! I'll display it in the zoo right away!

Hmm, that's too bad... If you change your mind, please let
me have it.

It seems the residents of Edo also love animals, as people
are coming to see them today as well. We will continue to
care for the animals with love. You are a person of merit
for our zoo. Thank you so very much!
My comrade was killed by a demon... Please avenge them...
Phew... It seems this horse is about to be retired soon.
I'm counting on you to take care of the horse.
What seems to be the problem?

Ah, recently this horse's strength has been fading. It's
getting old, so it might be time to retire it soon.
What!? You're going to get rid of this horse?

Yeah. But it feels too cruel to dispose of it, and I'm at a
loss...

If it's alright with you, could you let me take care of the
horse?

What!? You want this horse that's not even a fine steed?
Can't help it, I guess. But I can't just give it away for
free. Do you have something to trade?
Let's see... How about this lottery ticket?

Huh, a lottery ticket, huh? Alright, it's a deal. Take good
care of it. Thanks for everything up until now.

Hehe. The horse seems happy too. From today on, I'm your
owner.

--Karin traded the lottery ticket and acquired
\c[17]Horse\c[0]! (NextBeside Karin's home)

[Sign] Currently on a business trip at the Asakusa well--
Pharmacy

(I want some medicine for wounds, but it looks like the
shopkeeper is away on a business trip... Hmm, I should head
towards the Asakusa well.)

Thank you for your help at the well We sell various
medicines here. Which one would you like to purchase?
Thank you very much~ Please come again.

Hey, you there, girl. Have you seen the Mouse Komachi around?
The other day, my shop was burglarized. If you find her, let
me know. I'll recover every last coin that was stolen...!
Hey, girl over there! I need a word with you!

Eh!? (This man... he's the owner of the Sumiya store I
burgled the other day...)

Um... Do you need something from me...? (He hasn't realized
who I am, right? My heart's racing...)

Do you have a moment? Actually, I'm in trouble because a
painting I ordered hasn't arrived yet.

Yes. I commissioned a fusuma painting from an ukiyo-e artist
living in Edo Castle Town named Kaigetsudou, but it still
hasn't been finished. I'll give you 500 mon as a reward,
could you go and hurry them along for me?

Oh, that would be much appreciated. The place is called
[Ukiyo-e Workshop]. I'm counting on you then.

I'm counting on you to prompt for the painting. The place is
the Ukiyo-e workshop in Edo's castle town.

Sorry to keep you waiting. It seems that Kaigetsudou-san has
found his motivation, so he's going to rush the production
of the fusuma painting.

Oh! That's great news! I can't wait to see the finished
fusuma painting Here's an additional reward for your
success. Please accept it.

I'm looking forward to the completion of the fusuma
painting. Hehehe!
[Sign] Ueno Shiatsu Massage - 1000 Mon per session
[Sign] We buy rare animals at high prices

[Sign] The tiger in this zoo has been donated by the
generous lord.

We were stormed into the castle in the blink of an eye.
Despite our daily training, it's utterly shameful.

Ouch! My back hurts where the demon slashed it... Why... did
this happen to me...

Wow! Tigers are so cool! It's my first time seeing a real
one

Before I knew it, a splendid zoo has been built. This is
amazing!

Being able to see animals up close like this... it's
wonderful

It's so delightful to be able to see rare animals up close.
Look, Grandpa, a tiger! Such an impressive presence
Hey! Don't cut in line! I was here first!

I-I'm sorry! (I'll stop by the dance hall and then come
back.)

Alas... all the ingredients have spoiled. We'll have to
close for a while. Just when the shop was getting on
track... Momiji has stopped coming to the shop too. I wonder
if something happened?

If we're heading to the Fuma village, I shall join the
battle as well! Let's meet outside of Edo--

Even I can't hide my agitation... There are only a few days
left until the eruption. Next, we head to Fuji, Karin.
Kisanosuke-san! Are you safe as well?

Yeah. But is it true that the demons attacked? I haven't
seen it with my own eyes, so it's hard to believe...

...It's true. I never imagined they would seriously attack
Edo with an army. No, maybe I just didn't want to believe
it...

Is that so. But anyway, it's a relief that you're unharmed.
The clinic is like a field hospital with all the injured
samurai.
What about Kachou-san? I don't see her around?

Ah. Kachou is resting in bed. Actually... it seems she's
pregnant...

Ha ha! It's a bit embarrassing. Thanks. If I hadn't met you
on Mujou Island, I wouldn't have been able to return to Edo
and be with Kachou. I owe you a lot, Karin-san.

I have one more reason to protect Edo now. I'm off to the
final battle.

Oh, you're going to fight the demons? This is a parting
gift. There's not much because trade has stopped, but please
take it.

Thank you, Kisanosuke-san. Well then, see you again. Please
give my regards to Kachou-san and your mother-in-law.

Stay safe, Karin-san. Make sure you come back to Edo,
alright.

Be careful, Karin-san. You are strong. No matter what kind
of demon you face, you should never lose.
[Sign] New Specialty Toro Shop Now Open!

[Sign] No Trespassing - This Green Space is Private
Property--
Looks like we can finally get inside the shop.

We are already prepared. Let's head to Mount Fuji to defeat
Gyon.

I'm getting hungry while waiting, so I want to eat something
sweet soon.

I've been waiting in line for half an hour already... Eating
at a popular restaurant is such a hassle...

It only opened the other day, and it's already this crowded.
Edo folks just can't resist a good eatery, can they?

It's even a hot topic in the pleasure quarters. I heard it
was delicious, so I came all the way here to eat.

The poster girl here is super cute\I[15]She's dressed like a
fox, and the way she says "noja noja" is so amusing
Ugh... It seems like my arm bone is broken...
Hold on tight! The wound is shallow!?

So many injured people being brought in...! We must stop the
bleeding at any cost.
It's a terrible injury! Quick, get the bandages--!

I was attacked and tormented by demons, but miraculously I
survived. Ouch, ouch, ouch...

I was torn apart by claws in an instant, ending up like
this. The enemy was too strong... I never imagined I'd have
to fight a monster...
Don't speak! It will affect your wounds!

Who on earth did you fight with?! These are some serious
wounds!

Huh, a sushi restaurant opened in a place like this? A
specialty shop for tuna belly is quite unusual.
(A specialty shop for tuna belly? Could it be...)

(I'll make a wish to the Great Buddha for daddy to come home
soon...)
